HEADWORD: Muriform
<hw>Mu"ri*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>murus</ets> a wall + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Resembling courses of bricks or stones in squareness and regular
arrangement; <as>as, a <ex>muriform</ex> variety of cellular
tissue</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

